~ interaction_3
Lighthouse Keeper: Back Again?
MATE: Tell me more about this world.
Lighthouse Keeper: I guess I was wrong about the beauty thing... you truly are a thing of beauty. Wanna know why I had such a bad opinion of your kind?
MATE: Tell me.
Lighthouse Keeper: You're automatons, you're only meaning was to replace the working class, they worked their asses off just to get replaced by things made of stone and sorcery, old sorcery, it's all a scheme so the higher ups, like the guy you work for, get monopoly over this small community, why do you think there are so few of us left? or the houses so tiny and rare? They valued money over people they're slowly creating a world of money, this ain't our world anymore, the "despots" sold houses for raw material to trade between villages, the people have no power. Many of us left, by boat.
MATE: I'm sorry...
Lighthouse Keeper: You're not like the other automatons, you seem more... curious, maybe you can change something.
=> END

